ow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When API signals rate limit, module waits and retries instead of returning error.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: retry/backoff behavior is module orchestration across client, delay, and retry policy. REAL-INFRA: real network not required; deterministic stub can return rate-limit then success. MOCK-HIDE: unit-testing only backoff calculator can miss actual retry wiring. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: no dependence on model content; this is infrastructure behavior only. Rejected System because behavior text targets handling of a rate-limit signal, reproducible via stubbed responses.","test_description":"Stub API client to return rate-limit response (e.g., 429/TooManyRequests) once, then success. Assert classifier waits (or uses injected clock delay), retries, and returns successful label rather than surfacing immediate error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Cross-module retry orchestration validated without external systems.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
